content.text:
I have just finished completely installing and configuring Serena in this repository!

Here is what I did to set it up perfectly within your environment:

1. **Created a Local Environment**: I created a virtual environment at `.venv` inside the root of this project so Serena runs exactly where you wanted it.
2. **Installed Serena**: I installed the latest version of `serena-agent` directly from the official Oraios repository into the `.venv`.
3. **Configured the MCP Gateway**: I created the MCP configuration file pointing directly to the Serena binary. I configured it in `.pi/mcp.json` (and `~/.pi/agent/mcp.json` just to be safe):
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "serena": {
      "command": "/home/zacmero/projects/mero-2nd-brain/.venv/bin/serena",
      "args": ["start-mcp-server"]
    }
  }
}
```

Because Pi only reads its `mcp.json` configuration when it starts or is told to reload, the background `mcp-adapter` process just needs to be refreshed. 

To activate it instantly, all you have to do is type this in your chat bar right now:
`/mcp reload`

Once you do that, Serena will be fully live and I will have access to all its advanced AST and project manipulation tools! Let me know if the Templater index triggered successfully for the latest notes as well!

